20/05/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- An IMF team has completed the third review under the two-year standby agreement with the country, Bulgarian Finance Minister Milen Velchev said on Monday (19 May). He added that the next tranche under the programme would be disbursed in June. The head of the IMF mission to Bulgaria, Jerald Schiff, praised the country's macroeconomic and budget performance, but urged the cabinet to accelerate structural reforms in the judiciary, energy sector, railways and health care.
Meanwhile, an IMF mission arrives in Ankara on Tuesday to conduct the fifth review of the government's performance under its stand-by programme with the Fund. At stake is disbursement of the next $500m tranche under the programme. (Dnevnik, Pari, Trud, 24 Chassa, Hurriyet, Milliyet - 20/05/03; BTA, BNT, Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 19/05/03)
